the markings on them. You have to realize, when I

01:07.617 --> 01:14.423
got into this business, there was a huge 
controversy over the nature of the lunar craters.

01:14.583 --> 01:17.666
There were still people who wanted lunar craters 
and volcanoes. Kuiper was one of the first people

01:18.447 --> 01:29.337
who pointed out that lunar craters were different 
from lunar volcanoes and showed that these things

01:18.447 --> 01:29.337
that people would call them were genuine 
volcanoes like the volcanoes in Hawaii. and

01:29.873 --> 01:34.640
pointed that out as a result of compiling the 
pictures for the photographic data. And so there

01:35.462 --> 01:47.720
was a long period of techniques that were being 
used by mainline astronomers, particularly

01:35.462 --> 01:47.720
spectroscopy, simply weren't being applied to 
planets. And after planetary spectroscopy got

01:47.740 --> 01:58.817
revived, that quickly showed the need for more 
laboratory spectroscopy, more molecular

01:47.740 --> 01:58.817
things. molecular spectra have taken over an 
overriding importance in the Earth's atmosphere

01:59.135 --> 02:05.403
